<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 30" captionStartId="F30" captionText="Figure 30. Distribution map of Coccinia hirtella (pale yellow dots; based on 22 collections), Coccinia mackenii (blue triangles; based on 50 collections), and Coccinia quinqueloba (blue dots; based on 38 collections). For South Africa the borders of the provinces are given." pageId="81" pageNumber="82">30</figureCitation>
. Lesotho, South Africa (S KwaZulu-Natal, SE Free State). Afromontane scrubland and sourveld grassland. Elevation 110-1900 m. On sand, sandstone, loam, well-drained soils, full sun, grazing maybe tolerated.
</paragraph>
